# @forgesworn/range-proof — Cursor Rules

## Project

Pedersen commitment range proofs on secp256k1. Pure TypeScript, ESM-only. Runtime deps: @noble/curves, @noble/hashes.

## Commands

- Build: `npm run build`
- Test: `npm test`
- Typecheck: `npm run typecheck`

## Architecture

- `src/index.ts` — public re-exports
- `src/range-proof.ts` — main API (commitments, range proofs, age helpers, serialisation)
- `src/utils.ts` — crypto primitives (point arithmetic, generators G/H, hashToScalar)
- `src/errors.ts` — error hierarchy (RangeProofError > ValidationError, CryptoError)

## Crypto Safety

- NEVER modify Fiat-Shamir domain separators (pedersen-bit-proof-v1, pedersen-sum-binding-v1, pedersen-commitment-binding-v1)
- NEVER expose blinding factors in proofs or logs
- NEVER implement custom point arithmetic — use @noble/curves
- NEVER change the H generator derivation seed ('secp256k1-pedersen-H-v1')
- Always use scalarEqual() for scalar comparison (constant-time)
- Deserialisation must validate all hex inputs — do not weaken checks

## Conventions

- British English everywhere
- ESM-only — .js extensions in all imports
- Commit messages: type: description (feat:, fix:, chore:, refactor:, docs:)
- Semantic-release on main — work on branches
